# Vector illustrations for understanding

When building or improving user-facing flows (onboarding, dashboards, empty states, benefit/responsibility explainers, success moments), **generate simple visual vector illustrations** when they help the user understand faster than text alone.

## Prefer

- Theme-aware SVG/React illustration components colocated under feature or shared UI folders
- Use design-system / theme colors; avoid generic stock photos or emoji as the primary teaching visual
- One clear metaphor per illustration; keep size focused so copy stays readable
- Accessible labels on decorative teaching visuals

## Avoid

- Dense decorative art that competes with the message
- Skipping an illustration when the concept is abstract (commissions, referrals, moderation, verification)

## Example placement

Explainers (benefit / responsibility / how-it-works) should pair each section with a short illustration + title + one supporting sentence.
